      <bioghist id="aspace_24d4c313e0c447bc51230e9a0337a135">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Georges Claude May, specialist in French literature, was appointed to the Yale faculty in 1946, and was named dean of Yale College in 1963. He later served as provost of the university from 1979-1981.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_74a947417afd9745c4c7acea8ae8f135">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The papers are mostly comprised of administrative materials, speeches, and personal files, and document a small portion of Georges May's professional life, including his involvement with the Fourth International Congress on the Enlightenment, held at Yale in 1975.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
